Author: Shrabanti Chowdhury, Anna Xing, Pei Wang
Maintainer: Anna Xing <anna.xing@mssm.edu>
Description: CASPEN (celltype aware stacked pathway guided ensemble) is a
    toolkit for training and evaluating celltype-aware pathway-guided ensemble
    models, with functionality for pathway selection, gene selection, model
    comparison, and survival analysis. Users can specify input data, pathway
    definitions, celltype aliases, and modeling frameworks to build
    reproducible predictive workflows for binary, categorical, and survival
    outcomes.
